ExecDesc.value: Microsoft Windows Vista Feed Headlines Gadget Code Execution (IPv6 Version)

EngDesc.value: There exists a cross site scripting vulnerability in Microsoft Windows Vista Feed Headlines gadget. The vulnerability is caused due to lack of input validation when parsing RSS feeds. A remote attacker can exploit this vulnerability by convincing a target user to subscribe to a malicious RSS feed, potentially causing arbitrary code to be injected and executed in the security context of the currently logged in user. (IPv6 Version)
